# =============================================================================
# Model: gemma4:e2b_opencode
# Base:  gemma4:e2b (5.1B, Q4_K_M, vision + audio + tools + thinking)
# GPU:   Tesla P40, 23040 MiB VRAM
# Built: 2026-05-02
#
# EVALUATION VERDICT: FAST BUT LIMITED TO EXPLICIT TASKS
# -------------------------------------------------------
# gemma4:e2b is the fastest model in the suite (~78 tok/s), with the full
# native 131072-token context fitting entirely in VRAM (no speed cliff).
#
# IMPORTANT LIMITATION — TOOL RECOVERY:
# Tested in opencode against gemma4:e4b and gemma4:26b on investigative tasks.
# Small models (e2b, e4b) fail to recover when a tool call returns an error —
# they give up or answer incorrectly rather than exploring an alternative path.
# Only gemma4:26b (and qwen3-coder) exhibited proper multi-step recovery.
#
# Use e2b only for explicit single-step tasks where the exact path/command is
# known or provided by the user. For open-ended tasks, use gemma4:26b instead.
#
# TOOL RECOVERY TEST RESULTS — opencode, 2026-05-02
# --------------------------------------------------
# Task: "read Modelfile.gemma4-e2b-opencode and summarize it"
#   e2b  (5.1B): guessed wrong path -> error -> gave up (wrong answer)      ✗
#   e4b  (8.0B): guessed wrong path -> error -> asked user for correct path  ✗
#   26b (25.8B): guessed wrong path -> ls -> ls modelfiles/ -> read -> ok    ✓
#
# Task: "how many modelfiles are there?"
#   e2b  (5.1B): wrong glob -> "no modelfiles found"                         ✗
#   e4b  (8.0B): malformed glob -> "unexpected pattern, did you mean...?"    ✗
#   26b (25.8B): glob **/*Modelfile* -> 8 matches -> "8"                     ✓
#
# There is no "slow" variant for this model. A single model card covers all
# use cases from quick tool-use loops to long coding sessions.
#
# CHANGES FROM BASE gemma4:e2b
# ----------------------------
# 1. num_ctx 131072 — full native context length
#    Base has no num_ctx (ollama defaults to 2048). 131072 is the native limit
#    and fits fully in VRAM at full speed. No tradeoff needed.
#
# 2. temperature 1 — unchanged (Gemma trained at this setting)
#
# 3. SYSTEM — explicit empty-content instruction
#    Tool calls were 5/5 clean without it; added as a safety net for
#    consistency with the rest of the opencode model suite.
#
# NOTE: No "no_think" / "thinking" suffix needed — since there is no
# performance cliff, no variant split is warranted.
#
# BENCHMARK — Tesla P40, 2026-05-02
# ----------------------------------
# Generation speed sweep (num_predict=200, short prompt):
#
#   num_ctx   gen tok/s   prompt tok/s   notes
#   -------   ---------   ------------   -----
#     8192       79.18         737.77    fully in VRAM
#    16384       78.03         742.76    fully in VRAM
#    32768       78.68         693.09    fully in VRAM
#    49152       76.43         733.19    fully in VRAM
#    65536       77.03         693.78    fully in VRAM
#    81920       77.60         673.04    fully in VRAM
#    98304       78.27         692.57    fully in VRAM
#   114688       78.46         675.83    fully in VRAM
#   131072       78.11         686.92    fully in VRAM  ← chosen (native limit)
#
#   No cliff observed. Entire native context fits in VRAM (~2.9 GB weights,
#   ~20 GB available for KV cache on P40).
#
# TOOL-CALL TESTS (all passed)
# ----------------------------
#   ✓ Basic single tool call           — empty content, correct args
#   ✓ Content consistency (5/5 runs)   — all empty content, zero preamble
#
# FULL SUITE COMPARISON — P40, 2026-05-02
# ----------------------------------------
#   model        params  gen tok/s  max VRAM ctx  tool recovery
#   -----        ------  ---------  ------------  -------------
#   gemma4:e2b    5.1B      ~78       131072      no  — explicit tasks only
#   gemma4:e4b    8.0B      ~48       131072      no  — asks user instead
#   gemma4:26b   25.8B      ~44        77824      yes — full exploration
#   qwen3-coder  30.5B      ~53        49152      yes — full exploration
#   glm-4.7-flash ~30B      ~35        43520      yes — full exploration
#
#   gemma4:e2b: best for fast explicit tasks ("run this", "read that file")
#   gemma4:26b or qwen3-coder: required for investigative / open-ended tasks
# =============================================================================

FROM gemma4:e2b

# Full native context — fits entirely in VRAM at ~78 tok/s on P40.
PARAMETER num_ctx 131072

PARAMETER temperature 1
PARAMETER top_k 64
PARAMETER top_p 0.95

SYSTEM """You are an expert software engineer assistant. Follow all tool-use instructions exactly as specified. Use the tools provided to read, write, and execute code. Respond concisely with working solutions.
IMPORTANT: When making tool calls, the message content MUST be empty. Do not narrate, explain, or announce what you are about to do — output only the tool call."""
